{
  "_comment_purpose": "Explorer log matrix override for the CI test runs. Applied by the runner-validation-windows workflow (copied to %LOCALAPPDATA%\\Decentraland\\MetaForge\\log-matrix.json before mf explorer test). REPLACES the build's source-side matrix (ReportsHandlingSettingsProduction/Development) for the duration of the run.",
  "_comment_semantics": "isOverride=true -> this matrix is the sole source of truth for the CI run, independent of whatever the build's source-side matrix has enabled. EACH entry is one (category, severity) cell as enabled - matches the 2D inspector grid in unity-explorer (ReportsHandlingSettings asset). Categories NOT listed are FULLY silenced. When adding a new category to DCL.Diagnostics.ReportCategory, add 5 entries here (Log+Warning+Error+Exception+Assert) - or use `mf explorer log-matrix` interactively, which writes the same expanded form.",
  "_comment_tiers": "Default: full 5-severity coverage (Log+Warning+Error+Exception+Assert) for every category in DCL.Diagnostics.ReportCategory. Spammers observed in prior runs are demoted by 1 step - their Log severity is dropped, leaving Warning+Error+Exception+Assert (4 entries). No spammer was caught producing noisy Warnings on run 25917112690, so none demoted to Error.",
  "isOverride": true,
